==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[corona]]''', ''[[crown]]''

===Adjective===
'''coronary'''

# Crown-shaped, resembling or encircling as a crown, especially with regard to the [[artery|arteries]] or [[vein]]s of the [[heart]].

===Noun===
'''coronary''' (''plural'' '''coronaries''')

# A [[coronary thrombosis]] or [[heart attack]].
#: ''Manny had a coronary last week, followed by a triple bypass.''

===Translations===
*Swedish: [[kransartär]], [[hjärtattack]]

